- Constructor:
    - Check if a template called 'construct' is defined
        - Check all ctors and generate a union ctor
            - For now, pick just one
    - Or check all public ctors
- (public) Members:
    - If it's a Function<T> on_*, generate callback member
        - Somehow check if the existing member is made by us
            - Transfer its "old callback" to the current one
        - Set it to call the given JS function after the old callback
    - If it's a pair of functions called x() and set_x():
        - Make a native property with those
    - If it's a normal function
        - Make a function from that

- Type conversion:
    - Forwards:
        - Ptr<Object> -> WrappedObject
        - Numeric -> Number/BigInt (depending on type range)
        - String -> String
        - Anything else -> report an error and avoid it
    - Backwards:
        - WrappedObject -> Ptr<Object>
        - Number/BigInt -> Check type
        - String -> String
        - Anything else -> throw
